name: redis-py
raw_recipe:
{% set name = "redis-py" %}
{% set version = "2.10.5" %}
{% set build = 0 %}

package:
  name: {{ name }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: redis-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://github.com/andymccurdy/redis-py/archive/{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 159835ac5f09822bb3c578bdf848b9d137a67c2e4ae4b7aa05390dac33087def

build:
  number: {{ build }}
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - redis
  requires:
    - pytest >=2.5.0

about:
  home: https://github.com/andymccurdy/redis-py/
  license: MIT
  summary: Redis Python Client

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - kwilcox
    - daf
